\n<Manu><WordWrap>I think thats all the missing pages. Time to return to the Librarian to get my reward.
Head back to the library and return the lost pages to the Librarian
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Mayong aga. Are you one of the chaplain? I was sent here to help you feed the people.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>The guard tole me that you would tell me what to do.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Ah yes I am one of the chaplain of this church. So the guard at the Old Town Hall sent you? God Blessed you.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>You see we are short on food and we wanted to help feed the people here inside the plaza.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Can you help us feed these people?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Sure I can help you with feeding the people.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Are you familiar with Kare Kare? This is the dish we wanted to cook for the people but sadly we do not have the meal.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Can you help us make Kare Kare for the people?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>YEs, I will help you make this dish if I can find the recipe.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Ah if I recall the recipe is inside one of the houses in the Old Town Hall.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>If you can find the recipe and make Kare Kare, come back here so that we can divide the dish and properly distribute to the people.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>There is also a shop near by in the Old Town hall where you can buy all the ingredients you need to make Kare Kare.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Here is 1000 gold for you to buy the necesarry ingredients to make Kare Kare.
Head back to the Old Town Hall and search for Kare Kare recipe inside one of the buildings

Head to the shop in the Old Town Hall and buy ingredients to craft Kare Kare
Return to the Chaplain once you have crafted Kare Kare
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>There is a spare Kare Kare recipe in one of the houses near the Old Town Hall.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>There is also a shop in the Old Town Hall that has the needed ingredients for you to make Kare Kare
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Come back to me if you made Kare Kare.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Good now give it to me and we can now divide the dish.

The Chaplain divides the Kare Kare into multiple dishes
to distribute to the people of the plaza.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Here you go, I have finished distributing the dish into multiple meal packs. I want you to go into the different houses and give to each person who is in need.
Find people inside the plaza who is in need of meal packs and give it to them.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Come back to me if you have given all the meals to the people who are in need.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>There is a spare Kare Kare recipe in one of the houses near the Old Town Hall.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>There is also a shop in the Old Town Hall that has the needed ingredients for you to make Kare Kare
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Come back to me once you have crafted the dish so that we can divide it to the people.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>There is a spare Kare Kare recipe in one of the houses near the Old Town Hall.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>There is also a shop in the Old Town Hall that has the needed ingredients for you to make Kare Kare
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Come back to me once you have crafted the dish so that we can divide it to the people.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Come back to me if you have distributed the dish to the people who are in need.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>I have finished giving the people all the meal packs.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>I will inform the gurad what you did.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Thank you for helping out the church.
Report back to the guard that you have completed the task he has given to you.
\n<Chaplain><WordWrap>Return to me if you have finished giving out all the meal packs to the people.
